\begin_layout Subsection
Weight Average Molecular Weight
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sub:Weight-Average-Molecular"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The weight average molecular weight,
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w}$
\end_inset

, is similar to number average, but we use the distribution of weights instead
 of the distribution of molecules:
\begin_inset CommandInset nomenclature
LatexCommand nomenclature
symbol "$M_{w}$"
description "Weight average molecular weight"

\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Weight average molecular weight (
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w})$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
M_{w}=\frac{M_{0}{\displaystyle \sum_{N}}w_{N}N}{w}=\frac{M_{0}{\displaystyle \sum_{N}}w_{N}N}{{\displaystyle \sum_{N}}w_{N}}=\frac{M_{0}{\displaystyle \sum_{N}}n_{N}N^{2}}{{\displaystyle \sum_{N}}n_{N}N}\label{eq:Mw formal def}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The weight average degree of polymerization,
\begin_inset Formula $N_{w}$
\end_inset

, is obtained simply by dividing
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w}$
\end_inset

 by
\begin_inset Formula $M_{0}$
\end_inset

,
\emph on
i.e.

\emph default

\begin_inset Formula $N_{w}=M_{w}/M_{0}.$
\end_inset

 The polydispersity index
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
polydispersity index
\end_layout

\end_inset

, given by
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w}$
\end_inset

/
\begin_inset Formula $M_{N}$
\end_inset

 must be greater than or equal to one.
 Polymers with a polydispersity index close to 1 are said to be monodisperse,
 with a narrow distribution of molecular weights.
 While Eq.

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Mw formal def"

\end_inset

 is useful in a formal sense, it's a bit cumbersome to use.
 Suppose we have a series of molecular weight fractions, with
\begin_inset Formula $w_{i}$
\end_inset

 between the weight of each fraction and
\begin_inset Formula $M_{i}$
\end_inset

 being the weight average molecular weight of each fraction.
 The weight average molecular weight for this collection of molecules is
 given by the following summation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
M_{w}={\displaystyle \sum_{i}w_{i}M_{i}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

