\begin_layout Paragraph
Exercise:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Suppose 3g of a monodisperse polymer with M=50,000 g/mol is blended with
 5g of a monodisperse polymer with M=85,000 g/mol.
 What are the values of
\begin_inset Formula $M_{n}$
\end_inset

, and the polydispersity index for the resultant mixture?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Solution:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
To get
\begin_inset Formula $M_{n}$
\end_inset

, we need to divide the total weight of polymer (3g + 5g = 8g) by n, the
 total number of moles of polymer molecules:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula
\[
n=\frac{3g}{50,000g/mol}+\frac{5g}{85,000g/mol}=1.9x10^{-4}mol
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula
\[
M_{n}=\frac{8g}{1.19x10^{-4}mol}=67,200g/mol
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
The average molecular weight is obtained from the definition of this quantity:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
M_{w}=\frac{M_{0}\overset{\infty}{\underset{N=1}{\sum}}w_{N}N}{w}=\frac{1}{w}\overset{\infty}{\underset{N=1}{\sum}}w_{N}M_{N}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In our example, we obtain the following:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Formula
\[
M_{w}=\frac{1}{8g}(3g*50,000g/mol+5g*85,000g/mol)=71,875g/mol
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Polydispersity Index =
\begin_inset Formula
\[
\frac{M_{w}}{M_{n}}=\frac{71,875g/mol}{67,200g/mol}=1.07
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

