\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
What if the polymers in the previous example are not monodisperse? Suppose
 the molecular weights quoted are weight averages, the low molecular weight
 polymer has a polydispersity of 1.6, and the high molecular weight polymer
 has a polydispersity of 2.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Solution:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
We divide by the polydispersities to get number average molecular weights,
 and use these values to get the total number of molecules:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\[
M_{n}(poly.a)=\frac{50kg/mol}{1.6}=31kg/mol
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\[
M_{n}(poly.b)=\frac{85kg/mol}{2.5}=34kg/mol
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\[
n=\frac{3g}{31,000g/mol}+\frac{5g}{34,000g/mol}=2.44x10^{-4}mol
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\[
M_{n}(blend)=\frac{8g}{2.44x10^{-4}mol}=32,800g/mol
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Due to the form of the expression for the average molecular weight, we can
 modify the standard expression for the Mw by summing over all different
 components of the blend, and using the weight average molecular weight
 for each component:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
M_{w}(blend)=\frac{1}{w}\underset{i}{\sum}w_{i}M_{wi}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In our case
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w}$
\end_inset

 is the same as it was in the previous example:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\[
M_{w}=\frac{1}{8g}(3g*50,000g/mol+5g*85,000g/mol)=71,875g/mol
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align left
Polydispersity index =
\begin_inset Formula
\[
\frac{M_{w}}{M_{n}}=\frac{71,875g/mol}{32,800g/mol}=2.19
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

