\begin_layout Standard
Analytic expressions can be derived for number-average and weight average
 degrees of polymerization for ideal step growth polymerizations that follow
 the distribution described by Eq.

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:ideal nN  distribution for step growth"

\end_inset

.
 Substitution of this expression into Eq.

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Mn defintion (formal)"

\end_inset

 gives the following for
\begin_inset Formula $M_{n}$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
M_{n}=\frac{M_{0}\underset{N}{\sum}Np^{(2N-1)}}{\underset{N}{\sum}p^{(2N-1)}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
 We assume that our material is isotropic
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

,
\emph on
i.e.
\emph default
,
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

=1/2, 1, 3/2, 2, etc.
 Half integer values of
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 are allowed because
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 is the number of repeat units in the molecule.
 (A value of 3/2 for
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 would correspond to a molecule with one A monomer between two monomers,
 for example).
 Alternatively, we can replace
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 by
\begin_inset Formula $L/2$
\end_inset

, where
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 takes on all positive integral values:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
M_{n}=\frac{M_{0}}{2}\frac{{\displaystyle \sum}Lp^{(L-1)}}{{\displaystyle \sum}p^{(L-1)}}\label{eq:Mn sum - ideal stop growth}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We can follow a similar procedure to get an expression for
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w}$
\end_inset

.
 Combination of the ideal, linear step growth size distribution (Eq.

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:ideal nN  distribution for step growth"

\end_inset

) with the definition of
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w}$
\end_inset

 (Eq.

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Mw formal def"

\end_inset

), gives
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
M_{w}=\frac{M_{0}\underset{N}{\sum}N^{2}p^{(2N-1)}}{\underset{N}{\sum}Np^{(2N-1)}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
we can again let
\begin_inset Formula $L=2N,$
\end_inset

 so that
\begin_inset Formula $L$
\end_inset

 takes on all integer values, so that the expression for
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w}$
\end_inset

 becomes:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
M_{w}=\frac{1}{2}\frac{M_{0}\underset{N}{\sum}L^{2}p^{(L-1)}}{\underset{N}{\sum}Lp^{(L-1)}}\label{eq:Mw sum - ideal step growth}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These expressions for
\begin_inset Formula $M_{n}$
\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset Formula $M_{w}$
\end_inset

 can be simplified by using the following mathematical formulas:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
\begin{array}{c}
{\displaystyle \sum_{L=1}^{\infty}p^{L-1}=\frac{1}{1-p}}\\
{\displaystyle \sum_{L=1}^{\infty}Lp^{L-1}=\frac{1}{\left(1-p\right)^{2}}}\\
{\displaystyle \sum_{L=1}^{\infty}L^{2}p^{L-1}=\frac{\left(1+p\right)}{\left(1-p\right)^{3}}}
\end{array}\label{eq:standard sums}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Substituting the results for these sums into Eqs.

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Mn sum - ideal stop growth"

\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Mw sum - ideal step growth"

\end_inset

