 0.17g.
 Note that we need a lot less of A than B in this case.
 If we want our two component epoxy to consist of two parts that we combine
 in nearly equal volumes, we'll have to add some extra stuff to part A (the
 diamine part) that doesn't take part in the curing reaction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
To figure out the average functionality, we arrange Eq.

\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:nonlinear step growth average functionality"

\end_inset

 to give the following for
\begin_inset Formula $f_{av}$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
