\begin_layout Standard
A very useful way to think about the glass transition involves the concept
 of unoccupied space, or 'free volume' in a polymer.
 This concept is illustrated conceptually in Figure
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:free volume"

\end_inset

.
 The red dots connected together by lines represent polymer molecules.
 In this lattice model of polymers, the red dots are constrained to fit
 on a lattice.
 (The lattice is completely artificial, and does not exist in reality).
 These dots represent the '
\begin_inset Note Greyedout
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
occupied volume
\end_layout

\end_inset

'
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Occupied volume
