\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note that the linear thermal expansion coefficient, defined in terms of
 the linear dimensions of the sample rather than the volume, is equal to
 Î±/3.
 If the fractional change in free volume is small (
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta V/V\ll1$
\end_inset

