a.
 If we move the constraint that there are only 2 directions in which the
 walker can move, we get the example shown in Figure
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:2-D-Random-Walk"

\end_inset

b.
 These trajectories are now beginning to look like the shapes of actual
 polymer molecules, which is why this whole exercise is relevant.
\end_layout

