\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sub:Bond-Angle-Restrictions"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The freely rotating model is overly simplistic, because all bond rotation
 angles cannot be equally likely.
 At certain angles, functional groups attached to adjacent carbon atoms
 are too close to one another, as illustrated here.
\end_layout

