\end_layout

\end_inset

, the change in free energy of a system is equal to the work done on the
 system, provided that the process is reversible.
 In this example, an applied deformation force,
\begin_inset Formula $P_{z}$
\end_inset

, produces a small displacement,
\begin_inset Formula $d\ell$
\end_inset

.
 The work done on the system is
\begin_inset Formula $P_{z}d\ell$
\end_inset

, which is equal to the change in the deformation free energy change,
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta F_{d}$
\end_inset

:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\align center
\begin_inset Formula
\begin{equation}
P_{z}d\ell=d(\Delta F_{d})
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
