\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this case the stress is proportional to the strain, and the rate at which
 the strain is applied does not matter.
 As a result the time dependence of the stress looks just like the time
 dependence of the strain.
 The slopes of the time-dependent stress and strain curves (the top two
 curves in Figure
