\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In liquids the stress is proportional to the rate at which the strain is
 applied, and is independent of the current strain.
 Liquids do not store any strain energy, and as soon as the strain stops
 changing, the stress drops back to zero.
 The stress for the time dependent strain shown in Figure
