\begin_layout Standard
The spinodal curve
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Spinodal curve
\end_layout

\end_inset

 (or stability limit
\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Stability limit
\end_layout

\end_inset

) represents the boundary in the phase diagram where the the free energy
 of mixing changes from a positive curvature to a negative curvature.
 It occurs when
\begin_inset Formula $\chi=\chi_{s}$
\end_inset

, where
\begin_inset Formula $\chi_{s}$
\end_inset

 defines the spinodal curve.
 For
\begin_inset Formula $N_{a}=200$
\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset Formula $N_{b}=300$
\end_inset

 the spinodal curve is shown as the dashed line in Figure
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
